article.headline: Alabama State 56, Miss. Valley St. 52
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Ralfeal Golden scored 16 points to lead Alabama State to a 56-52 victory over Mississippi Valley State University on Monday. Golden shot 2-of-5 from 3-point range and led the Hornets (8-12, 6-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference) with eight rebounds. Richard Lott also hit 2-of-5 3-pointers and had 10 points for the Hornets. Dustin Richmond and LaMarquis Blake each had a game-high three assists. The Hornets trailed 26-20 at halftime but came back to score 36 points in the second half to seal the win. The team shot 30.5 percent from the field. Ronald Alexander led the Devils (8-12, 6-5) with 12 points and a game-high 11 rebounds. Jessie Taylor added 11 points for the Devils and Kelvin McCoy had 10. The team hit only one 3-pointer out of 20 attempts and shot 33.8 percent from the field.
